body.description: No job is too big, no pup is too small! Luvs diapers with new Paw Patrol designs have your back—and their butts. Luvs now has up to 12 hours of protection, day and night. Like Chase and Marshall would say, our highly trained paws are at your service. And diaper leaks? We’re on the case with nonstop leak protection. Luvs Triple Leakguards absorb quickly to help stop diaper leaks before they happen. But our leak protection doesn’t stop there. Secure cuffs and stretchy sides keep leaks locked in where they happen the most. Forget about cheap, leaky diapers and spend more time enjoying this ride known as parenting. With Luvs you know when they go, thanks to a wetness indicator that turns blue on contact with wetness. You care what your baby wears, so Luvs diapers are 100% hypoallergenic, made free of parabens and free of latex* (*natural rubber). When it comes to the ultimate diaper protection, these paws uphold the laws. Our diapers are so good, you don’t need this, but Luvs does offer a money-back guarantee. If you aren’t fully loving your Luvs diapers, we will gladly send you a refund. See luvsdiapers.com for terms and conditions.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars We love Luvs!
reviews.reviewText: With the price of everything going up, we decided to try these instead of our usual Huggies brand. They look a bit flimsy but are surprisingly very strong. My baby has had no leaks even after wearing all night. Maybe not a good choice for babies who have lots of blowouts though. These are a great value got the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are just as good as the expensive ones!
reviews.reviewText: I am the mom in the Luvs commercial. For my first kid, I stuck to Huggies and Pampers because I wanted only the best for my baby. Then one day I was at the store and just grabbed some Luvs. They were thinner than the other brands, so I was skeptical at first. But we used them and loved them. No issues, no leaks, great coverage of the poops. So for my second kid, we started with the Luvs. He wears these to bed and during the days. I don't think they leak overnight any more than some of the more expensive brands, even the ones specifically for overnight. Highly recommend not wasting your money on more expensive brands. These are great,

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These are the best diapers. I have never had a problem with leakage or rashes with these diapers. My daughter has sensitive skin and these diapers are perfect for her. The fit on her is perfect. They absorb quickly to pull it away from her body and the leak protection is amazing. I will only use these diapers for all my children. I highly recommend these diapers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars OH MY GOD
reviews.reviewText: Ok look I’m not the kind to write a review on diapers. I’ve been using this brand off and on for years. But I ran straight here after what just happened.Imagine my horror when I realized a USED DIAPER ended up in the laundry? (It was just pee thankfully)I opened the lid and there on top was the diaper, bloated and angry. My heart SANK expecting to rewash that load all night trying to get the absorbent filler out of my clothes. But nothing. It didn’t even break a little?!? When I tell you the washer was on HEAVY SOIL and it’s a TOP LOAD WASHER!!! My friends… this is easily the most impressive diaper I’ve come across. Further, it’s so absorbent that I am now positive, based on the size and heft, neither of the twins will ever be able to pee through a diaper. I was already a subscribe customer, but I will tell this story when I start recommending them to others from now on.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good and cheap
reviews.reviewText: I've used Luvs off and on for the last four years and never had a glaring problem with them. Occasionally they've leaked but I have had the occasional leak from every brand I've tried so that's not a big deal. I recently updated our subscribe and save from size 4 to size 5 in Luvs. The box we got was the Paw Patrol design while previous boxes had been the earlier design and I don't know what they did, if it has to do with the sizing, designs, or what but the tabs on these are garbage. I've had several come off in my hand while trying to put a diaper on and on multiple occasions, one side has failed while my son was wearing it and the diaper came off. If they're cutting costs for my kids to be able to pee on Chase and Marshall then I really wish they would return to better quality and less recognizable designs. Unfortunately, I've got a box coming and we'll have to use those but I will be changing our subscription. Hopefully the quality improves soon because Luvs has always been a budget friendly and reliable option. I'm hoping I just ended up with a bad batch this first go around with the size 5 Paw Patrol diapers.One positive, no leaking as long as the diaper stays on.Update: looks like we had gotten a defective box! Which is a relief because I do like Luvs. I just wish I'd realized it sooner because the company has a 30 day policy about returning unsatisfactory diapers - according to the box. Will keep on keeping on with these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: 99% of the time these are the best priced on Amazon. When looking price per diaper. I like that it has the gel, holds well for during the day. Overtime we stopped using them as over nights.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The very best. Easiest to get on a crazy moving baby.
reviews.reviewText: I have 4 kids. These are the best! We started with another brand. Then, you get to the point where your child tries to wrestle you everytime you change their diaper. If they rolled off the new diaper you are trying to get on mid diaper change, (of other brands) the diaper springs up and you lose. Back to square one. These are less springy so you can lay them flat and they stay like that so strapping them to a wiggle worm becomes much easier! Trust me! The easiest diaper to get on your kid. Also, we didn't have problems with leaks in these either. Luvs for life.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Our go to brand for 8 years!
reviews.reviewText: Our youngest is a year and oldest is 8. All of our kids have been in Luvs diapers until they were potty trained. We like the price and they don’t irritate my babies skin like other brands did. A brand that starts with p and end with amper. They don’t hold urine over night as well as other brands though.
Buenos pañales cumplen con lo descrito

reviews.reviewTitle: Le dio alergia a mi bebé de 8 meses
reviews.reviewText: Llegaron súper rápido y en buen estado. Pero al segundo día de usarlos le dio alergia a mi bebé. Los suspendí inmediatamente y los devolví. En cuanto los deje de usar se le quitó a mi bebé el rush . Y ya su piel esta como siempre en excelentes condiciones! No los recomiendo. Por querer ahorrar sale peor. Ya no cambiare los pampers por ningún pañal…
